org.apache.commons.rdf.rdf4j

Class RDF4JParserBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.commons.rdf.simple.AbstractRDFParserBuilder<RDF4JParserBuilder>
      • org.apache.commons.rdf.rdf4j.RDF4JParserBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, RDFParserBuilder

    public class RDF4JParserBuilder
extends AbstractRDFParserBuilder<RDF4JParserBuilder>
implements RDFParserBuilder
    RDF4J-based parser.

    This can handle the RDF syntaxes RDFSyntax.JSONLD, RDFSyntax.NQUADS, RDFSyntax.NTRIPLES, RDFSyntax.RDFXML, RDFSyntax.TRIG and RDFSyntax.TURTLE - additional syntaxes can be supported by including the corresponding rdf4j-rio-* module on the classpath.

      • createRDFTermFactory

        protected RDF4JTermFactory createRDFTermFactory()
        Description copied from class: AbstractRDFParserBuilder
        Create a new RDFTermFactory for a parse session.

        This is called by AbstractRDFParserBuilder.parse() to set AbstractRDFParserBuilder.rdfTermFactory(RDFTermFactory) if it is Optional.empty().

        As parsed blank nodes might be made with RDFTermFactory.createBlankNode(String), each call to this method SHOULD return a new RDFTermFactory instance.

        Overrides:
        createRDFTermFactory in class AbstractRDFParserBuilder<RDF4JParserBuilder>
        Returns:
        A new RDFTermFactory

      • prepareForParsing

        protected RDF4JParserBuilder prepareForParsing()
                                        throws IOException,
                                               IllegalStateException
        Description copied from class: AbstractRDFParserBuilder
        Prepare a clone of this RDFParserBuilder which have been checked and completed.

        The returned clone will always have AbstractRDFParserBuilder.getTarget() and AbstractRDFParserBuilder.getRdfTermFactory() present.

        If the AbstractRDFParserBuilder.getSourceFile() is present, but the AbstractRDFParserBuilder.getBase() is not present, the base will be set to the file:/// IRI for the Path's real path (e.g. resolving any symbolic links).

        Overrides:
        prepareForParsing in class AbstractRDFParserBuilder<RDF4JParserBuilder>
        Returns:
        A completed and checked clone of this RDFParserBuilder
        Throws:
        IOException - If the source was not accessible (e.g. a file was not found)
        IllegalStateException - If the parser was not in a compatible setting (e.g. contentType was an invalid string)

        Description copied from class: AbstractRDFParserBuilder
        Parse AbstractRDFParserBuilder.sourceInputStream, AbstractRDFParserBuilder.sourceFile or AbstractRDFParserBuilder.sourceIri.
